Professor I have a question from the last lab! I changed my branch to ReuseLoop and committed the changes. I see that I pushed a branch named ReuseLoop in Github. Do I have to change my branch to master?
It is also curious to me
You can't change your ReuseLoop branch into master but you can merge it if you like your current change. If you don't like the ReuseLoop brach, you can delete it. Do you want to learn how to merge?
Oh then why can't I change my branch?
which branch?
in where?
In eclipse!
Do you want to switch your branch from ReuseLoop to master?
Um.. I am curious about the differenece between pushing with ReuseLoop and with master.

You can just keep two source code in git. You can unlimited variations of your program. You can implement experimental features of your program and if you like it you can merge the branch with master. In this way, your program can be improved. This is how developers work with git branches.
multiples developers work for different features in different branches and then we can merge all the branches so that we can complete our program together.

Oh, so programmers can make their own branches which are like copies of the source code. When they modify the code and commit changes with the branches, the code editor decides whether to merge or not. And if we work with the master branch and commit the changes, there is no need to merge because it is the master branch.
Do I understand correctly?
Yes.
Oh I get it! Thank you so much, sir!
You may read this article. http://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/
